{
  "database": {
    "technology": "PostgreSQL 15",
    "models": [
      {
        "name": "User",
        "fields": {
          "id": "Integer (Primary Key)",
          "email": "String (Unique, 255 chars)",
          "hashed_password": "String (255 chars)",
          "created_at": "DateTime (default now)"
        }
      },
      {
        "name": "Task",
        "fields": {
          "id": "Integer (Primary Key)",
          "title": "String (255 chars)",
          "description": "Text (nullable)",
          "status": "Enum (todo, in_progress, done)",
          "priority": "Enum (low, medium, high)",
          "due_date": "Date (nullable)",
          "user_id": "Integer (Foreign Key -> User.id)",
          "created_at": "DateTime (default now)",
          "updated_at": "DateTime (default now)"
        },
        "relations": [
          "Many-to-One avec User"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "instructions": "Oumeyma, cr\u00e9e les mod\u00e8les SQLAlchemy avec les champs ci-dessus. Utilise les types Enum pour status et priority. Impl\u00e9mente les relations avec back_populates. Ajoute des indexes sur user_id, status et priority pour optimiser les filtres."
  },
  "backend": {
    "technology": "FastAPI (Python 3.10)",
    "endpoints": [
      {
        "path": "/auth/register",
        "method": "POST",
        "description": "Inscription d'un nouvel utilisateur",
        "auth_required": false,
        "request_body": {
          "email": "string",
          "password": "string"
        },
        "response": {
          "access_token": "string",
          "token_type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/auth/login",
        "method": "POST",
        "description": "Connexion d'un utilisateur existant",
        "auth_required": false,
        "request_body": {
          "email": "string",
          "password": "string"
        },
        "response": {
          "access_token": "string",
          "token_type": "string"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks",
        "method": "GET",
        "description": "Liste des t\u00e2ches avec filtres",
        "auth_required": true,
        "query_params": {
          "status": "optional enum",
          "priority": "optional enum"
        },
        "response": {
          "tasks": "array of Task objects"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks",
        "method": "POST",
        "description": "Cr\u00e9ation d'une nouvelle t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "request_body": {
          "title": "string",
          "description": "optional string",
          "status": "optional enum",
          "priority": "optional enum",
          "due_date": "optional date"
        },
        "response": {
          "task": "Task object"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "method": "GET",
        "description": "R\u00e9cup\u00e9ration d'une t\u00e2che sp\u00e9cifique",
        "auth_required": true,
        "response": {
          "task": "Task object"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "method": "PUT",
        "description": "Mise \u00e0 jour d'une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "request_body": {
          "title": "optional string",
          "description": "optional string",
          "status": "optional enum",
          "priority": "optional enum",
          "due_date": "optional date"
        },
        "response": {
          "task": "Task object"
        }
      },
      {
        "path": "/tasks/{task_id}",
        "method": "DELETE",
        "description": "Suppression d'une t\u00e2che",
        "auth_required": true,
        "response": {
          "detail": "string"
        }
      }
    ],
    "auth": {
      "approach": "JWT avec python-jose (JWS) et passlib (bcrypt pour le hachage)",
      "token_expiration": "30 minutes",
      "security_scheme": "OAuth2PasswordBearer"
    },
    "instructions": "Akram, structure le backend en routers s\u00e9par\u00e9s (/auth et /tasks). Utilise FastAPI's dependency injection pour l'authentification. Impl\u00e9mente les services users_service et tasks_service avec les m\u00e9thodes CRUD. Ajoute des tests unitaires pour chaque endpoint avec pytest. Utilise SQLAlchemy en mode async pour les requ\u00eates."
  },
  "frontend": {
    "technology": "React 18 + TypeScript + Vite",
    "components": [
      {
        "name": "AuthProvider",
        "description": "Contexte d'authentification avec gestion du JWT"
      },
      {
        "name": "LoginForm",
        "description": "Formulaire de connexion avec validation"
      },
      {
        "name": "RegisterForm",
        "description": "Formulaire d'inscription avec validation"
      },
      {
        "name": "Dashboard",
        "description": "Page principale avec liste des t\u00e2ches et filtres"
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskList",
        "description": "Composant affichant les t\u00e2ches avec pagination"
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskItem",
        "description": "Composant pour une t\u00e2che individuelle avec actions (\u00e9diter/supprimer)"
      },
      {
        "name": "TaskForm",
        "description": "Formulaire de cr\u00e9ation/\u00e9dition de t\u00e2che"
      },
      {
        "name": "FilterBar",
        "description": "Barre de filtres par statut et priorit\u00e9"
      }
    ],
    "pages": [
      {
        "path": "/",
        "component": "Dashboard",
        "protected": true
      },
      {
        "path": "/login",
        "component": "LoginPage",
        "protected": false
      },
      {
        "path": "/register",
        "component": "RegisterPage",
        "protected": false
      }
    ],
    "instructions": "Mactar, cr\u00e9e une SPA avec React Router v6. Utilise Material-UI pour les composants UI. Impl\u00e9mente un contexte d'authentification pour g\u00e9rer le JWT. Cr\u00e9e des hooks personnalis\u00e9s pour les appels API (useTasks, useAuth). Ajoute des tests avec React Testing Library. Utilise Vite pour le bundling avec configuration optimis\u00e9e pour TypeScript."
  },
  "auth": "JWT avec python-jose + passlib bcrypt",
  "cache": "none",
  "message_broker": "none",
  "container": "Docker + Docker Compose avec services pour frontend, backend, database et pgAdmin",
  "cloud": "D\u00e9ploiement local pour d\u00e9veloppement, cible AWS ECS pour production"
}